Hari terakhir MSC 2022 baru saja berakhir, dengan membawa hasil RSG Filipina menjadi juara pertama di Asia Tenggara, menyingkirkan tahta sang Raja, RRQ Hoshi dari Indonesia di fase Grand Final. 

Sangat disayangkan sekali, Raja dari para Raja belum berhasil menumbangkan dominasi Filipina di Asia Tenggara. MSC Cup dimenangkan oleh Emann dan kawan-kawan dan dibawa pulang oleh mereka.

Selama pertemuan pertama antara kedua tim ini, RRQ Hoshi berhasil menyingkirkan juara MPL PH dengan skor 3-1 untuk mencapai Grand Final MSC 2022. RSG Phillipines harus melalui final lower bracket dan mengalahkan rekan senegaranya SMART OMEGA untuk mencapai Grand Final.

Namun, seolah-olah tim yang berbeda, permainan dari RSG Phillippines terlihat berbeda dan lebih terencana dengan jelas. Pada 2 game pertama, RRQ Hoshi masih bisa mengimbangi permainan RSG PH. Namun karena kesalahan fatal, tim Filipina berhasil mencuri kemenangan atas RRQ Hoshi.

Pada kedudukan 2-0, sang raja raja harus mengambil kembali momentum dari RSG Phillippines dengan strategi baru. Namun ibarat buku, semua pergerakan tim Indonesia terbaca sampai akhir. RSG Phillippines menyelesaikan Grand Final dengan cara anti-klimaks dengan skor 4-0 tanpa balas.

Hal ini tentu menjadi sebuah kekecewaan bagi para fans Mobile Legends tanah air, terlebih bagi para fans team yang sering disebut Raja ini. Tapi dibalik kekecewaan itu, semua sepertinya setuju, kualitas tim Filipina tidak boleh dipandang sebelah mata. Semoga kedepan tim Indonesia bisa mendominasi lagi lewat belajar dari kesalahan mereka.

Juneteenth celebrates Black resilience.

We’d like to celebrate the end of industrial slavery—but it continues (and has outrageously only expanded) across the entire U.S. through our nation’s fascist prison system.

Read the 13th Amendment. Slavery remains legal in the United States in 2022, and in fact is now more widely practiced than it was before the Civil War.

Our criminal injustice system is a horror in plain sight that too many Americans refuse to acknowledge.

Z4pnu merupakan salah satu pemain aktif Smart Omega. Pemain veteran asal Filipina ini merupakan salah satu sosok yang paling dicari oleh para penggemar Mobile Legends Indonesia karena ucapan-ucapannya yang kontroversial. 

Semua berawal ketika ia menilai bahwa pemain publik Filipina saat ini bisa mengalahkan pemain pro Indonesia. Kemudian disusul dengan pendapat tentang Smart OMEGA yang lebih kuat dari RRQ Hoshi.

Ada beberapa klarifikasi yang ia lakukan di tengah-tengah momen tersebut, namun tetap saja ia seakan menjadi public enemy para penggemar MLBB Indonesia sekarang. Di sisi lain, meski masuk dalam roster Smart Omega, Z4pnu belum juga diturunkan di MSC 2022. Tentu saja, publik bertanya kapan sosok ini bisa menunjukkan aksinya selain membuat pernyataan.

"Saya sangat ingin bermain, tapi saya menunggu keputusan P4kbet (pelatih). Tapi saya tidak ingin melawan RSG PH, saya juga tidak ingin melawan Falcon. Tapi saya ingin melawan RRQ karena di sana ada Skylar dan Alberttt," ujar Z4pnu dalam sesi wawancara media usai mengalahkan Orange.

Sang pelatih menambahkan, tentu saja Z4pnu akan bermain tapi harus menunggu momen yang tepat. "Z4pnu menunggu waktu yang tepat untuk bermain karena dia adalah pengambil keputusan resmi di tim, jadi kita tunggu saja nanti."

Semoga saja, Smart Omega masih memiliki peluang untuk menang melawan Falcon nanti. Karena jika mereka kalah, Z4pnu pasti akan menjadi sasaran komentar pedas dari netizen.

Amazon deforestation grows -

Between January and April 2022, the accumulated amount is 1.954km² of felled forest. It is a mark 69% above the same period in 2021.

The most devastating states with the environment:
Amazonas - 347 km²;
Pará - 287 km²;
Mato Grosso - 242 km².

The alert is from INPE (National Institute for Space Research).

This deforestation is predominantly illegal, the result of theft on public lands.

 "The context forms a 'perfect storm: three years of impunity, reduced control, inspection and assessment, aggravated by a permissive and electoral discourse", says Raul Valle, director of socio-environmental justice at WWF-Brasil.

_ Incredible how humans, in terms of devastation, resemble locusts.
Some profit, it's true!
But it is worth remembering that, while a few groups profit from the devastation of the forest, all others lose.

Kabar cukup mengejutkan datang dari tim RRQ, yang mengumumkan perpisahannya dengan veteran Tank, William "Liam" Setiawan, pada tanggal 13 Juni 2022 melalui akun Instagram dan kanal YouTube resminya.

Perpisahan Liam dengan tim RRQ inipun terjadi tanpa adanya rumor yang biasanya beredar di permukaan media sosial. Tank legendaris yang sudah menjadi panutan sejak MPL S2 ini berpisah dengan tim yang sudah tumbuh bersamanya selama kurang lebih 4 tahun. 

Tidak ada keterangan dari pihak tim terkait keputusan ini, namun William menegaskan bahwa ini adalah keputusannya setelah debut terakhirnya di MPL ID S8 & MPLI 2021.

Tidak heran mengingat peran Liam di team sebagai Roamer telah digantikan dengan Vyn dalam beberapa waktu terakhir. Dia juga gagal membawa tim untuk memenangkan kejuaraan di pertandingan terakhirnya. Kendati demikian, Liam telah mencapai banyak prestasi luar biasa selama karirnya di franchise MPL bersama sang team, RRQ.

VYN sendiri, sebagai pengganti Liam di lineup Roam, telah memenangkan gelar juara dan MVP di MPL ID S9 menggunakan Franco khasnya. Potensi VYN tampaknya akan bersinar musim ini. Di sisi lain, kelanjutan dari karir Liam selanjutnya masih belum diketahui. Dan saaat ini posisinya adalah Free Agent, jadi ia berpotensi bergabung dengan tim lain atau istirahat hingga batas waktu yang tidak ditentukan.

Sebagai informasi, Liam sudah rehat bersama Xinn sejak MPLI berakhir meski masih berada di organisasi tersebut. Pada akhirnya, dia memutuskan untuk keluar dari organisasi tersebut saat MSC 2022. Cukup sedih mendengar hal ini ya, COMEBACK STRONGER Liam!

MSC 2022 kini tengah berlangsung dan kabar mengejutkan datang dari tim IDONOTSLEEP Esports atau IDNS yang akan bertanding di turnamen MSC 2022. Kabarnya salah satu staf pelatih tim asal Thailand tersebut adalah seorang wanita asal Indonesia.

Berita mengenai wanita Indonesia yang menjadi pelatih tim IDNS mulai mencuat ke permukaan pada beberapa waktu lalu. Seorang wanita Indonesia bernama Niszenav adalah sosok yang dikabarkan akan menjadi pelatih tim IDNS.

Sosok Niszenav sendiri sebenarnya bukanlah pemain baru di scene kompetitif Mobile Legends. Ia tercatat pernah membela tim Imperial Esports yang sekarang sudah berganti nama menjadi Impunity Imperial ID.

Awal mula Niszenav bergabung dengan tim Thailand ini berawal dari keterlibatannya dalam scrim match yang sering dimainkan tim IDNS. Niszenav kebetulan mengenal Panda sebagai pelatih tim RSG.PH, yang sering menjadi lawan scrim tim IDNS. Panda menyarankan agar ia bergabung dengan tim INDS.

Menurut Panda, tim IDNS mengalami peningkatan performa yang sangat signifikan setelah Niszenav membantu tim tersebut. Panda berpendapat bahwa kinerja tim IDNS meningkat sembilan puluh persen, dan sering menyulitkan tim RSG PH setelah kehadiran perempuan asal Indonesia tersebut.

Niszenav akhirnya memutuskan untuk bergabung dengan tim Thailand, dan turnamen MSC 2022 akan menjadi turnamen pertama Niszenav bersama tim IDNS. Semoga kak Niszenav bisa terus berkiprah di Pro Scene Mobile Legends ya!

Kabar buruk bagi para fans ONIC Esports, perjalanan mereka di MSC 2022 berlangsung sangat singkat. Pada hari pertama group stage, ONIC yang berada di grup A pada pertandingan pertama bertemu Falcon dari Myanmar. Diunggulkan sebagai juara MPL Season 8, mereka secara mengejutkan malah dikalahkan mudah dengan skor 2-0.

Kekalahan tersebut menjadi sangat fatal bagi ONIC karena format group stage pada MSC kali ini akan mengeliminasi tim terbawah dari setiap grup. Situasi ONIC dalam situasi terdesak ini menuntu mereka harus menang sempurna di match terakhir melawan tuan rumah, Todak. Sayangnya, tim Malaysia tersebutpun mampu menahan imbang ONIC sehingga berdasarkan poin ONIC menjadi tim terbawah di grup A.

Kekalahan ini tentu sangat mengecewakan bagi para fans mereka. Hal itu juga menunjukkan betapa berbahayanya setiap peserta karena satu kesalahan bisa berakibat fatal. Menurut para pemain Todak, kekalahan dan hasil buruk ONIC ini karena meta pada patch kali ini tidak cocok untuk gameplay ONIC.

"Kami sebenarnya yakin menang melawan ONIC 2-0, karena kami sudah mempelajari gameplay ONIC dan mereka memang kurang beradaptasi dengan patch ini. Jadi lebih mudah untuk melawan ONIC saat ini," kata 4meyz mewakili rekannya dalam sesi wawancara after match.

Apa yang dikatakan 4meyz sepertinya benar adanya. Sanz yang biasanya menggunakan hero marksman atau assassin sepertinya kurang leluasa ketika menggunakan META hero tank jungler. Gameplay farming yang biasa digunakan ONIC pada meta sebelumnya harus diubah dengan permainan objektif yang cepat.

Cukup mengecewakan mendengengar kabar ini ya, semoga RRQ tidak melakukan kesalahan yang sama pada MSC ini, dan tetap semangat buat ONIC dan para fans!

From The Nation: 
“This is just what happens when a woman accuses a rich and powerful white man of sexual and domestic violence. Such a woman must be a perfect victim—or maybe simply perfect—to avoid becoming the target of a smear campaign against her on the Internet….

The legal travails between Depp and Heard began in 2018, when Depp sued The Sun for libel in the UK. The British tabloid called him a “wife beater” after Heard initiated divorce proceedings and obtained a restraining order against him in May 2016. The judge, Andrew Nicol, ruled that “the great majority of alleged assaults of Ms. Heard by Mr. Depp have been proved to the civil standard” of being more likely than not to be “substantially true.” It is striking—and telling—that Depp lost the libel suit in the UK, where the burden of proof is on the defendant to show they haven’t committed libel, rather than on the complainant to prove their accusations.”

🚨 Arms companies still prioritize profits over people. This must stop! 
Today we filed a criminal complaint with the Judiciary Tribunal in Paris against French arms manufactures Dassault Aviation, Thales and MBDA France. Together with Mwatana for Human Rights & Sherpa – supported by Amnesty International France – we demand investigations into the criminal liability of the corporations for their possible complicity in war crimes and crimes against humanity allegedly carried out by #SaudiArabia & the #UAE in #Yemen. 
Despite a war waging for over 7 years & an abundance of documented attacks on civilians by #SaudiArabia & the #UAE, European companies still are delivering weapons & military support to the warring parties. The French judiciary could set an important example by opening thorough & serious investigations into the practices of the French arms industry. #Impunity must not prevail. The people of #Yemen deserve #justice & #accountability.

Intimidation, Blackmail, Oppression, Bullying and Impunity in broad day light to the glare of everyone.

I’m forced to agree with "Joao Lourenco"  who said “Corruption happens because there is Impunity. That’s the reason corruption is widespread at all levels – From the person who asks for a small bribe on the street to those who hold prominent positions and misuse power and office.

As a Lagosian and a citizen of this country, I sometimes wonder if there is hope for the less opportune as I don’t like to use the word "poor" . 

How does the Less opportune feel inclusive in a country like Nigeria. During my teenage years, I was an ardent reader of TELL Newspaper and I remember back then the stories I use to read… I lived with the hope that things will get better as we grow older but unfortunately I gradually came to the realization that the reverse is the case.

Beyond this remarks, it is for a fact that the political discourse on Impunity does not directly address its structural causes, but it rather addresses the individuality of each citizens and how he/she has chosen to live or define his character.

It is time for us as a Nation to device a means of ending or eradicating impunity in our society, otherwise the culture of Impunity will be reinforced on a daily basis thus weakening the hope in the Justice system and encouraging the repetition of the same offenses if not worse.

I can not but imagine the impunity of those responsible for acts resulting to serious human rights violations, inflicting pain and suffering on victims, bullying, oppressing and intimidating fellow citizens yet makes it seem like immunity is  for them that have attained a level of success and affluence. 
What A Country! What A People!!

We need to understand that impunity must be collectively  fought as a matter of Justice for the victims, which will then serve as a deterrent to prevent subsequent and new violations and fundamentally to uphold the rule of law and public trust in the justice system, including where there is a legacy of serious human rights violation.
The Lord Help Us all as a Nation!

Signed
Adeyinka Igbinoba

L’Union européenne et ses États membres devraient prendre des mesures concrètes pour renforcer le système de justice internationale, notamment en engageant des poursuites au niveau national pour les crimes relevant du droit international.

Les États membres devraient étendre la portée de la justice en adoptant les législations nécessaires, en créant ou en renforçant les unités spécialisées dans les crimes de guerre, en renforçant la coopération entre États et en apportant un plus grand soutien financier et politique à la Cour pénale internationale (#CPI) et aux autres mécanismes d’établissement des responsabilités afin qu’ils puissent accomplir leur travail en toute impartialité.

Katie Babson a écrit un article court et convaincant sur l'écocide en tant que cinquième crime.

"L'écocide est une cause profonde de l'urgence climatique à laquelle la communauté internationale est confrontée et est un contributeur principal au changement climatique. C'est une question si importante parce que l'écocide et ses contributions dévastatrices au changement climatique ont été perpétués pendant des décennies par #BigOil et les sociétés adjacentes, ainsi que par les dirigeants politiques qui ont refusé de prendre des mesures réelles.

"Ce mécanisme juridique (modifier le Statut de Rome de la Cour pénale internationale pour ajouter l'#écocide comme un crime) est un moyen de lutter contre l'impunité, de demander des comptes et d'empêcher les dommages de se produire, offrant "une occasion sans précédent de créer une législation mondiale qui pourrait dissuader les dirigeants imprudents de rédiger délibérément des politiques dommageables à court terme."

"Une telle criminalisation servirait de base morale et juridique par laquelle les contributeurs au changement climatique et donc à la destruction des écosystèmes naturels seront condamnés par la communauté internationale."

Lire l'article sur le site de l'UCSD Climate Change Review (lien dans notre linktree).

Mexican families and human rights groups demand authorities do more and take action over the crisis of missing or disappeared people. ⁣
⁣
"Having a disappeared son, a daughter or a relative is death in life," said a mother whose son is missing.⁣
⁣
On Tuesday, Mexico's Interior Ministry officially registered over 100,000 people as missing or disappeared. This information has been recorded since 1964.⁣
⁣
But experts say there could be many more missing people. Some victims may not be reported because of fear or other circumstances, as organized crime is mainly responsible for the disappearances.⁣

Katie Babson wrote a short and compelling article about ecocide as the #FifthCrime. 

“Ecocide is a root cause of the climate emergency the international community faces and a main contributor to climate change. This is such an important issue because ecocide and its devastating contributions to climate change have been perpetuated for decades by #BigOil and adjacent corporations, as well as political leaders who have refused to take real action.“

This legal mechanism (amending the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court to add #ecocide as a crime) is a way to fight impunity, seek accountability and prevent harm from happening, providing “an unprecedented opportunity to create global legislation that could deter reckless leaders from willfully drafting damaging short-term policies.”

“Such criminalization would serve as a moral and legal baseline whereby contributors to climate change and thus the destruction of natural ecosystems will be condemned by the international community.”

Read the article on the UCSD Climate Change Review @ucsdclimatereview 

.

25 indigenous people disappeared after complaints of violence and death by miners against a Yanomami teenager and child, aged 12 and 3.

Their village was burned to the ground. On the 5th of May, the Yanomami were found far from where they used to live. So far, it is not known who burned the place or what actually happened.

The silence of the Brazilian media and government in the face of the complaints mobilized part of the population, who asked for justice for the crimes. 

It is worth mentioning that this is not an isolated case. It is the result of 522 years of forced colonization, violence, and impunity.

Escola molt antiga, onada molt nova.
*†*
Extortion consists of obtaining property from another through the wrongful use of actual or threatened force, violence or fear. Such #coercive extortion is synonymous with the term blackmail, which is an older term used to indicate extortion. Common law jurisdictions also refer to a second type of extortion, extortion "under colour of office" or "under colour of official right", which is the wrongful taking by a public officer of money or property that is not due to him/her, whether or not the taking was accomplished by force, threats, or use of fear.

Besides some exceptions, such as in the case of extortion "under colour of office" or "under colour of official right", the act required for extortion is the threat of future harm. Generally, extortion #statutes require that a threat must be made to the person or property of the victim. The nature of the threatened harm varies by jurisdiction, and it can include bodily harm, damage to property, damage to reputation, criminal accusations, or abuse of a public office. The extortionate threat required must be serious enough to place a #reasonable person in fear. The actual obtainment of money or property is not required to commit the offence.

In many jurisdictions, the intent to take money or property to which one is not lawfully entitled must exist at the time of the threat in order to establish extortion. In other words, making the threat is sufficient and the actual obtainment of money or property is not required to commit the offence.

Extortion is different from the crime of #robbery: in robbery, the property is taken against the will and without the consent of the victim, while in extortion the victim consents, although unwillingly, to surrender money or property. Another distinguishing factor is that the nature of the threat for robbery is limited to an immediate #physical harm to the victim. Extortion, on the other hand, encompasses a greater variety of threats relating to future harm (Neumann and Elsenbroich, 2017).

NOT ME SERIES Appreciation Post

Part 1: The theme of Not Me Series

Its genre are Action, Thriller, Mystery, Romance. The topics discussed in each episode are different but meaningful and educational, related to the society issues, meaning of life and other values. For instance, the topics on EP. 2 (Freedom is the oxygen of the soul), EP. 4 (Impunity), EP. 5 (YOLO), 6 (Value of Life), EP. 7 (Marriage Equality) and EP. 11 (Power) are remarkable for me!👏👏👏 Of course, there are still other good topics they discussed in the series.👍👍

Furthermore, it passed on some practical knowledge🧑‍🔧🧑‍🏭 like how to wash off gasoline, how to deal with tear gas and gun wounds, how to utilize internet public opinions etc.

The director of this series also wants this series to be a role model for the Thai entertainment industry workers, that being brave to voice out the important and essential social issues and problems, changing the industry ethos to bring a new vision.

The whole series is sort of expressing the right ideas, positive attitude and energy to the world, its influence is not only in Thailand, but also in other places. Therefore, Not Me Series is a series that well balancing with elements of education and entertainment.

It’s #WPFD2022

Not sure there is much to celebrate as journalists across the world are killed, unjustly imprisoned, silenced, intimidated, and impunity enjoyed by the perpetrators is sickening. 

But then I think of all the brave journos out there who remain vigilant and continue their work despite all the challenges. 

So I’m going to celebrate them. That they exist, and that they keep inspiring others. It’s a privilege to know some of them. 

And I would like to remember all those who have passed including those whose names we don’t even know. 

On this World Press Freedom Day just like on any other day, I hope to see a world and live in a time where we, journalists, can do our job, without harassment, threats, and restrictions.

#Kachin state has experienced the #Burma military's counterinsurgency campaigns for decades in order to claim control of the state's natural resources. In 1994, the KIA signed a ceasefire that lasted for 17 years before #armedconflict erupted once again in 2011 when the Burmese military broke the ceasefire and attacked the KIA. 

As #armedconflict raged throughout the state, the Kachin suffered numerous #humanrightsabuses at the hands of the Burmese military. Tens of thousands were displaced as a result of the fighting. They also suffered #rape, #sexualviolence, #murder, & #torture. Civilians were also forced to be #porters & #humanshields. Children were often forced into military service as #childsoldiers. 

The international community must turn words into action. The Burmese junta is immune to resolutions. It only emboldens them to commit #humanrightsviolations with #impunity. Without tangible action, we will only see more #warcrimes, more #crimesagainsthumanity, and quite possibly another #genocide.

John Lennon returned his MBE in protest at British foreign affairs.
#watercolour from the original 1969 letter 

In 1969 Lennon had sent identical letters addressed to the Queen, the Prime Minister, and the Central Chancery saying his action was “in protest against Britain’s involvement in the Nigeria-Biafra thing, against our support of America in Vietnam, and against Cold Turkey slipping down the charts.” The letter was signed “With love, John Lennon,” in his handwriting.

The letters were written on notepaper headed Bag Productions, the company Lennon had recently set up with Yoko Ono.

”Police, the military, and the Department of State Services (DSS) reported to civilian authorities; but periodically acted outside civilian control.

”The national police, army, and other security services sometimes used force to disperse protesters; and apprehend criminals and suspects. Police forces engaging in crowd-control operations generally attempted to disperse crowds using nonlethal tactics; such as firing tear gas, before escalating their use of force.

“Human rights violations, corruption; and extrajudicial crimes by officials of the Nigerian security forces have remained a concern; with several reports highlighting a large number of Nigerians who are being targeted regularly.”

I was finally ready to surrender to the fact I was powerless over cocaine and concede that I never would have power over cocaine or any other mind altering substance the fight had gone from my mind and body. 

I had to acknowledge the fact that I wasn't like others and that I would never be able to use cocaine with impunity. 

More than that I had to surrender to the fact that I couldn't live life on my own self will or my terms as that hadn't served me well at all. 

Admitting this to my self felt like a defeat. The abolishment of my self will. 

But that relinquishment of control something that I would have expected to be a source of fear and anxiety achieved quite the opposite. 

Surrendering my self will has brought me a feeling of tranquility and for the first time that I can remember and I now feel at peace with myself and with life. 

I realise now I had to stop fighting and loose the battle in order to win the war 🙏🏻💪🏻
